# Testing

## Tests are the spec

- When adding or modifying functionality, write automated tests that prevent
  regressions and document the supported features/workflows.
- Tests are the durable spec — comments and docstrings supplement them, never replace.
- Add the test in the same commit as the functionality (and its regression class).

## Prefer real over mocked

- Prefer real inputs and outputs over mocks — sit as close to actual user behavior as
  possible. The harness adapts to the production shape; don't reshape production solely
  to expose internals for testing.

## Running tests

- Invoke the test runner via `my-mise-en-place` (e.g. a mise-managed `pytest`), not a
  bare binary. Lint/validate alongside via `my-linting`.
